              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Deuterons were momentum analyzed in a double",
                " focusing magnetic spectrometer."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PS",
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Deuterons were detected in the focal plane",
                " with a 10 cm x 2.5 cm double-sided position sensitive",
                " silicon detector covered with a 42 mg/cm**2 Ta foil",
                " to stop beam particles that otherwise might strike",
                " the detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two 5 cm x 1.7 cm silicon detectors used for",
                " detection of alpha particles, one detector on either",
                " side of the beam, each detector divided into 25 strips",
                " At small angles, the detectors were covered with a 9",
                " mg/cm**2 Ni foil at 33 MeV and a 10.7 mg/cm**2 Ni",
                " foil at 42 MeV to stop elastically scattering beam",
                " particles."
              ]
            }
          ],
